review_blob: Strong cherry aroma dominants with low levels of ashy roasted malt. Flavor is strongly dominated by ashy roasted malt with notes of unsweet chocolate and dark roast coffee. Cherry flavor lingers in the back. Rating is due to overtly strong ashy character and bitter roast notes.
beer_name: Quest Rum Barrel Aged Chocolate Cherry Stout.

review_blob: Big piney notes and rich candy orange citrus in the nose, poured with dense thick head that stays. Strong piney sap notes and enough caramel malt backbone to stand up to intense hop flavor in the flavor. Slightly sticky sweet finish.
